column1: OMAP-35: Organ Mapping Antibody Panel (OMAP) for Multiplexed Antibody-Based Imaging of Human Brain with Cell DIVE

column24: rationale
Nuclear marker for mature neurons; widely used for neuron identification.
Enzyme for GABA synthesis; identifies inhibitory neurons.
Complementary to GAD2; also marks inhibitory neurons.
Used to detect GAD1; see above.
RNA-binding protein involved in neuronal differentiation and plasticity.
Pan-astrocyte marker; more comprehensive than GFAP for astrocyte labeling.
Identifies axons. Key component of CNS myelin; used to assess myelination.
Identifies oligodendrocyte progenitors and mature oligodendrocytes.
Involved in synaptic plasticity; enriched in dendritic spines.
Intermediate filament protein, labels vasculature and reactive glial states.
Classic marker for astrocytes, particularly reactive subset; also used to assess reactive gliosis.
Lysosomal marker for activated microglia and macrophages.
Axonal marker; used to assess axonal integrity and neurodegeneration.
Cytoplasmic marker across all cell types for help with cell segmentation.
Calcium-binding protein highly expressed in a subset of inhibitory interneurons
Marker for presynaptic terminals; indicates synaptic density and activity.
Myelin-associated enzyme; marker for oligodendrocyte maturation.
Marker for microglia and macrophages; used to assess neuroinflammation.
Dendritic marker; used to assess neuronal morphology and dendritic integrity.
